# ============================================================================
# Morph — root .gitignore
#
# This repo's public surface is: the engine (src/, tests/, CMakeLists.txt,
# the vendored Fathom tablebase source), the distributed compute platform
# (platform/, distributed/), and documentation (README.md, CONTRIBUTING.md,
# SECURITY.md, docs/, platform/docs/). Everything below is either a build
# product, generated data/state, a large third-party binary, or an unrelated
# side project — see PUBLICATION_PREVIEW.md for the reasoning behind each
# block.
#
# platform/.gitignore and distributed/.gitignore already cover their own
# runtime state (venvs, __pycache__, sqlite3 db files) and are left as-is;
# this file does not duplicate those rules.
# ============================================================================

# --- Build output ---
/build/
/buildD/
/out/
CMakeCache.txt
CMakeFiles/

# --- Unrelated side project (own repo, own project notes; not part of
#     this publication at all — see python-engine's own "repo split" note) ---
/python-engine/

# --- Large third-party reference/opponent engine binaries.
#     Kept on disk at repo root today so local benchmarking scripts can
#     reference them by absolute path (see DEVELOPMENT.md's "repo split" note),
#     but these are other projects' compiled releases (Stockfish, Lc0,
#     Berserk) and their supporting archives/DLLs — not this project's
#     source, and not ours to redistribute from this repo. ---
/stockfish/
/stockfish-windows-x86-64-avx2.zip
/lc0.exe
/lc0-v0.32.1-windows-cpu-dnnl.zip
/berserk.exe
/baseline.exe
/cutechess-1.5.1-win64/
/dnnl.dll
/mimalloc-override.dll
/mimalloc-redirect.dll
/mimalloc-readme.md
/mimalloc-LICENSE
/DNNL-LICENSE
/DNNL-THIRD-PARTY-PROGRAMS
/791556.pb
/791556.pb.gz

# --- Generated training data, checkpoints, run artifacts, and other
#     machine-produced output (not source, regenerable, in several cases
#     multi-hundred-MB) ---
/experiments/
# models/ — trained .nnue/.json nets. Not required at runtime: the engine
# defaults to classical eval, and NNUE::init() builds an in-code
# material-baseline net automatically even if none is loaded.
/models/
/results/
/snapshots/
/training_server/datasets/
/tools/nnue_pipeline/runs/
/tools/nnue_pipeline/data/
/tools/nnue_pipeline/nets/
/tools/nnue_pipeline/checkpoints/
/tools/nnue_training/smoke_run_evidence/
/automation/generated/
/automation/logs/
/automation/state.json

# --- Python runtime/build state, anywhere in the tree ---
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.venv/
venv/

# --- Local databases (also covered inside platform/ and distributed/, kept
#     here as a catch-all) ---
*.sqlite3
*.sqlite3-wal
*.sqlite3-shm
*.sqlite3-journal

# --- OS / editor / IDE cruft ---
desktop.ini
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.vs/
.vscode/
*.user

# --- This publication-review process's own working documents. Written for
#     local/private review (internal reasoning, "your standing approval"
#     phrasing, etc.) -- not meant to ship as part of the public repo. ---
/PUBLICATION_PREVIEW.md
/DISTRIBUTED_COMPUTE_AUDIT.md
/DISTRIBUTED_COMPUTE_COMPLETION_REPORT.md

# --- Local-only dev notes alias (mirrors DEVELOPMENT.md); never published. ---
/CLAUDE.md
